RATIONALE: Lorazepam, diphenhydramine hydrochloride, and haloperidol gel, when absorbed into the skin, may be an effective treatment for nausea and vomiting.

PURPOSE: This clinical trial studies lorazepam, diphenhydramine hydrochloride, and haloperidol gel in healthy volunteers.

